01/09/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The OSCE Mission to Serbia-Montenegro denounced on Wednesday (31 August) the murder of Slavoljub M. Scekic, deputy head of the criminal police department and head of the general crime department at the Montenegrin Interior Ministry.
Montenegrin police say they have detained over 40 people in connection with the murder.
Scekic was gunned down Tuesday morning near his home in Podgorica.
He had been working on a number of high profile cases.
In other news Wednesday, UNMIK announced that a third UN police member has been arrested on suspicion of human trafficking.
Two others were detained last week in Kosovo on charges of smuggling people into the province.
(OSCE Web site, Mina - 31/08/05)
